ProtoDefines:
. "A function $f$ is \term{ piecewise continuous } on $[a,b]$ if
   \begin{alist} \item $f(x_0+)$ exists for all $x_0$ in 
   $[a,b)$; \item $f(x_0-)$ exists for all $x_0$ in $(a,b]$; 
   \item $f(x_0+)=f(x_0-)=f(x_0)$ for all but finitely many 
   points $x_0$ in $(a,b)$. \end{alist} If c fails to hold at 
   some $x_0$ in $(a,b)$, $f$ has a \term{ jump discontinuity at 
   $x_0$ }. Also, $f$ has a \term{ jump discontinuity at $a$ } if
   $f(a+)\ne f(a)$ or \term{ at } $b$ if $f(b-)\ne f(b)$."
